# Regenerated by the ESP-IDF component manager on every build. Committing it
# is normally fine for reproducibility, but the entry for the locally-
# vendored waveshare/esp32_s3_touch_amoled_2_06 component gets recorded with
# an ABSOLUTE filesystem path (source.path) baked in at lock time — works
# only in the checkout that generated it, breaks in any other one (this is
# exactly what broke firmware-ci: it was generated in a devcontainer at
# /workspaces/waveshare_amoled_smartwatch and committed, which CI's
# different checkout path can't resolve). Let every environment regenerate
# its own correctly-pathed lock instead of committing one.
dependencies.lock

